ScarCity — Project Handoff Summary
What it is
Unity 6 (URP, 6000.3.6f1) 3D city game inspired by Dispatch. Top-down orthographic camera. STEM-teaching minigames triggered by crisis events on a city map. 3-minute timer, HP system, score = f(HP, time). Made by Grade 8 students.
Scene Setup

ScarCity.unity — main city scene. SimplePoly City asset pack. ~1044 prefab instances. Ortho camera at (400, 130, 140), 25° tilt, size 90. URP. No scripts attached to city scene yet — still building it.
EarthquakeTriangulation.unity — separate 2D minigame scene. Ortho camera at (0,0,-10).
Both scenes registered in Build Profiles.

Scripts Written
Core Systems (not yet placed in scene)

GameManager.cs — singleton, DontDestroyOnLoad, owns timer/HP/score. Score formula: MAX_SCORE × (hp/maxHP) × (0.5 + 0.5 × timeLeft/totalTime)
CrisisSpawner.cs — spawns CrisisMarkers on city map at escalating rate
CrisisMarker.cs — clickable popup, countdown timer, calls MinigameBridge
MinigameBridge.cs — singleton, handles scene transitions to/from minigames, pauses global timer
MinigameResult.cs — abstract base class for all minigame scenes, call Succeed() or Fail()
CityHUD.cs — drives timer/HP/score UI

Earthquake Minigame (built, partially tested)

GridBackground.cs — procedural km grid via LineRenderers, needs LineMaterial (Sprite-Lit-Default URP shader)
SeismicStation.cs — uses new Input System (IPointerDownHandler etc), draws radius line + circle, snaps to 0.5km grid
EarthquakeMinigame.cs — 3 stations, circumcircle method to find epicenter, acceptable error 2.5km. Stations at (-6,4), (5,5), (0,-6). Actual epicenter (1.36, 0.87). Inherits MinigameResult.

Traffic System (working in ScarCity scene)

Waypoint.cs — graph node, has nextWaypoints, isExit (red gizmo), isStop (blue gizmo) with stopChance/minStopTime/maxStopTime
CarAgent.cs — follows waypoints, random speed variation, handles exit/stop logic via coroutine
CarSpawner.cs — spawns cars at entry waypoints every spawnInterval seconds up to maxCars, despawns at exit waypoints

